node.title: Watch Live: Kentucky governor holds briefing on tornado aftermath
node.description: At least 88 people died in a weekend outbreak of severe storms and tornadoes, including at least 74 in Kentucky.
node.content: ["Kentucky Governor Andy Beshear is giving an update on devastating tornado damage in his state four days after what he called \"the worst tornado event\" in Kentucky's history. Michael Dossett, director of Kentucky Emergency Management, is also expected to speak at the briefing, which is scheduled for 12 p.m. Eastern.", "The confirmed death toll from the outbreak of storms and tornadoes that lashed the central U.S. has continued to rise since Friday night. Beshear said Monday at least 74 people were killed in his state and it may take weeks before the final death toll is known.\u00a0", "At least 14 other people were killed in Arkansas, Illinois, Tennessee and Missouri.\u00a0", "President Biden is traveling to Kentucky on Wednesday to assess the damage."]
